Description: Small fragment of seal-impression showing uneven impressions at the rear which are obscured by the dirt which was not cleaned away before the object was hardened. Possibly an impression of a string. The fine brown Nile clay has inclusions of mica particles. The front shows parts of a larger seal impression, only the central part is preserved and finger impressions around it are visible. Three columns of text are visible, the left: [n]Tr nfr [nb] tAwi, middle: cartouche of Men-kheper-ra (Mn-khpr-R')|, right: [...] rn(?) mn?.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
